5000|$|The <b>Bank</b> <b>of</b> <b>Latvia</b> {{has issued}} two {{collector}} coins featuring {{the imagery of}} the 5 lats coin. The first was struck in 2003 {{as part of the}} international series The Smallest Gold Coins of the World. The second was struck in 2012 to commemorate the 90th anniversary of the bank. The <b>Bank</b> <b>of</b> <b>Latvia</b> worked with the British Royal Mint, which minted the original coins, to recreate the coin using electrotypes used in minting the original coins.|$|E
40|$|The {{purpose of}} the {{research}} {{is to find out}} the main factors that determine customer loyalty and the choice <b>of</b> a <b>bank</b> in <b>Latvia.</b> To achieve the goal the following research methods have been used: a questionnaire, quantitative and qualitative methods, including the methods of sociologic research and the descriptive method. By analysing scientific literature and the results of research conducted in the foreign countries, the authors have proposed and tested four hypotheses, three of which have been approved (H 2 -H 4), but one has been rejected (H 1). The data obtained in the research confirme that there is interrelation between empirical research carried out abroad and the results obtained in the <b>banks</b> <b>of</b> <b>Latvia...</b>|$|R
