5000|$|In 1561, {{during the}} Livonian Wars, the Livonian Confederation was {{dismantled}} and the Livonian Brothers of the Sword, {{an order of}} German knights, was disbanded. On {{the basis of the}} Treaty of Vilnius, the southern part of Estonia and the northern part <b>of</b> <b>Latvia</b> were ceded to the Grand Duchy of Lithuania and formed into the Ducatus Ultradunensis (Pārdaugavas hercogiste). The part <b>of</b> <b>Latvia</b> between the west <b>bank</b> <b>of</b> the Daugava River and the Baltic Sea became the Duchy of Courland and Semigallia, nominally a vassal state of the King of Poland Ruled by the Dukes from the House of Kettler with the exception of Peter von Biron ...|$|R
